52
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:19,550
- May I get your help?
- Sure.

53
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:22,020
So... scented candles.

54
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:24,060
Give me your thoughts on these scents.

55
00:03:24,060 --> 00:03:27,800
- That's more interesting to you than flowers, right?
- Yes.

56
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:32,220
That smells good.

57
00:03:33,470 --> 00:03:35,440
And not appetizing, right?

58
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:37,640
Hey.

59
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:41,240
Smell these candles and tell me what you think.

60
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:44,550
I will do that.

61
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:48,700
I like this one.

62
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:52,120
We now offer a new variety of ring boxes.

63
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:54,150
Please pick whichever color you'd like.

64
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:57,610
They're all so pretty!

65
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:59,360
Which one should I get?

66
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:02,090
- They seem to be a hit.
- Yes.

67
00:04:02,090 --> 00:04:05,990
By the way, Kotaro-kun dropped off dried flowers the other day.

68
00:04:05,990 --> 00:04:09,210
- Yes, I heard.
- Is that so?

69
00:04:10,130 --> 00:04:15,020
Thank you again for turning my ring into a necklace.

70
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:19,760
- Of course.
- It served as my good-luck charm, but...

71
00:04:21,850 --> 00:04:25,730
Then we will contact you once the box is complete.

72
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:27,830
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

73
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:30,290
I can't wait!

74
00:04:30,290 --> 00:04:32,930
Thank you, please come again.

75
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,500
How many does that make?

76
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:39,870
She was the fourth.

77
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:41,250
The fourth what?

78
