This is starting to really hurt.

126
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:09,440
It hurts!

127
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:14,330
Darn it!

128
00:08:36,990 --> 00:08:38,790
What are you doing?

129
00:08:40,540 --> 00:08:42,580
I was wondering if they'd have a scent.

130
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:44,510
A delicious scent, maybe?

131
00:08:44,510 --> 00:08:47,060
Those are edible flowers, after all.

132
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:48,930
- Wait, seriously?
- Yes.

133
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:53,580
But don't eat those. Edible ones need to be properly cultivated.

134
00:08:53,580 --> 00:08:55,300
I won't.

135
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:58,440
I didn't realize there were so many edible flowers though.

136
00:09:02,650 --> 00:09:05,150
- It's okay.
- Sorry?

137
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:10,430
Come by even if you don‚Äôt find the flowers pretty or aren‚Äôt buying anything.

138
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:15,110
Okay.

139
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:24,610
<i>It smells melancholic, but also quite good.</i>

140
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:34,050
Honestly, I didn't think they smelled particularly good.

141
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:40,670
But if I ever find flowers pretty,

142
00:09:40,670 --> 00:09:44,450
I might enjoy the changing seasons even more.

143
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:46,320
I guess.

144
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:49,120
Then I'll look forward to it.

145
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:53,270
Are you jealous? I‚Äôve still got my first experience to look forward to.

146
00:09:53,270 --> 00:09:55,130
I admit, I am.

147
00:09:55,130 --> 00:09:57,010
I knew it.

148
00:09:57,010 --> 00:09:59,740
- Shall we get going?
- Sure.

149
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:05,900
Something smells good.

150
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:09,930
- Crepes?
- No, it's waffles.

151
00:10:09,930 --> 00:10:12,450
Can you tell the difference by how they smell?

152
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:15,140
Of course, I can.

153
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,700
- What is it?
- There was a bug.

154
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:28,460
Even as a florist, are you scared of bugs?

155
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:31,450
I'm not scared; I just don't like them.

156
00:10:31,450 --> 00:10:35,430
Sounds rough. Flowers have plenty of bugs around them, right?

157
00:10:35,430 --> 00:10:38,020
It's not rough at all.

158
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:44,960
Which are you eyeing? The strawberry or this one?

159
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:49,600
The plain? I'm thinking chocolate or custard.

160
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,480
Sounds good.

161
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:54,040
- Here you go.
<i>- Thank you.</i>

162
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,180
<i>Let's eat.</i>

163
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:01,350
- This is really good.
- So is mine.

164
00:11:01,350 --> 00:11:04,070
- You have cream all over your face.
- No, I don't.

165
00:11:04,070 --> 00:11:06,170
So do you.

166
00:11:07,260 --> 00:11:09,010
So good!

167
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:10,630
Are you still eating?

168
00:11:10,630 --> 00:11:12,010
Try this one, too.

169
00:11:12,010 --> 00:11:13,670
I already had some.

170
00:11:13,670 --> 00:11:16,700
I want you to have another. It's really good.

171
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:21,550
Still good.

172
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:23,630
Right?

173
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:27,200
So you prefer to share the food you like.

174
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:30,380
Yes, because I want to share the joy too.

175
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,780
Then I'll have another.

176
00:11:33,780 --> 00:11:35,520
Hey!

177
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,890
Delicious.

178
00:11:36,890 --> 00:11:39,620
- How's yours?
- It's just okay.

179
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:42,050
- Thanks.
- Hey!

180
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:44,850
You're stuffing yourself.

181
00:11:44,850 --> 00:11:46,740
<i>Maybe add this sauce.</i>

182
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:49,200
<i>Okay, even better.</i>

183
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,680
- This is so cute.
- Looks just like you.

184
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:54,070
- No, like you.
- How?

185
00:11:54,070 --> 00:11:56,520
Flower shaped... sugar?

186
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,330
- Did you make this too?
- Of course not.

187
00:11:58,330 --> 00:11:59,640
It's cute.

188
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:01,430
I wanted a ring.

189
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:02,550
Is that so?

190
00:12:02,550 --> 00:12:04,360
This is good.

191
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,400
- It really suits you.
- It's cute. It looks nice.

192
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,850
It's cute.

193
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:13,030
I found something that would suit you.

194
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:15,990
Really? Let's check it out.

195
00:12:26,010 --> 00:12:29,100
I appreciate the gift, but why an umbrella? It's not raining.

196
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:32,210
- I just wanted to get it for you.
- But why?

197
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,810
I just felt like it.

198
00:12:34,810 --> 00:12:37,480
If you say so. Thanks.

199
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:40,280
Want something to drink?

200
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:44,610
Sure. I'll pay, as thanks for the umbrella.

201
00:12:44,610 --> 00:12:49,640
I'm not letting a younger, amnesiac, gluttonous artisan trainee treat me.

202
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,960
Must you call me "gluttonous"?

203
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:58,260
- Is anything okay?
- I'll take an iced latte with low fat milk and extra sugar.

204
00:12:58,260 --> 00:13:02,150
"Low fat"... okay.

205
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:11,560
Could I get an iced latte with... This.

206
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:15,230
- This low...
- Low fat milk?

207
00:13:21,130 --> 00:13:24,980
<i>Would you like to join us for coffee?</i>

208
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:32,870
<i>"Love makes even faults look charming."</i>

209
00:13:38,110 --> 00:13:40,690
- Here's your drink.
- Thanks.

210
00:13:41,540 --> 00:13:44,550
- Oh, a ladybug!
- What?

211
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:48,290
- Did I step on it?
- Looks like it flew away.

212
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:59,720
The receptionist at the clinic I visit is my doctor's younger sister.

213
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:05,840
Her name is Chigusa-san, and she is really charming. And she said...

214
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:09,240
What?

215
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,900
- Sensei?
- What?

216
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:13,670
That's my doctor I just mentioned.

217
00:14:14,770 --> 00:14:17,230
- Sensei.
- Ogata-san?

218
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:23,360
- Is everything all right?
- Actually, Chigusa-san has gone missing.

219
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:26,140
I was keeping a careful eye on her,

220
00:14:26,140 --> 00:14:30,800
but she may have forgotten her way here.

221
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:33,020
- We'd like to help find her.
- Oh, no.

222
00:14:33,020 --> 00:14:38,580
It's fine; she has my number for emergencies.

223
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:41,160
I'm certain she's nearby.

224
00:14:44,010 --> 00:14:45,850
Let's look for her together.

225
00:14:45,850 --> 00:14:48,360
- But...
- Do you have a picture of her?

226
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:51,050
Do you know places she may visit?

227
00:14:51,050 --> 00:14:52,700
Thank you.

228
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:57,200
Here... h-here is a picture of her.

229
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:03,280
Chigusa-san has early-onset dementia.

230
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:06,000
I don't think she will recognize me,

231
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:09,680
even if I walk by.

232
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:20,200
Let's split up to cover more ground. I'll go this way.

233
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:23,270
- Have you seen this woman?
- No.

234
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:25,260
I see. Thank you.

235
00:15:25,260 --> 00:15:30,980
Excuse me. Have you seen this woman?

236
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:35,590
Chigusa...

237
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:43,290
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

238
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:44,760
Have you seen this woman?

239
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:47,580
Excuse me. I'm currently searching for someone.

240
00:15:47,580 --> 00:15:51,680
Excuse me, have you seen this woman by any chance?

241
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,890
Here you go.

242
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:57,370
- Here...
- Excuse me. I'm actually looking for someone.

243
00:15:57,370 --> 00:16:00,490
Have you seen this woman around the area?

244
00:16:00,490 --> 00:16:02,910
Thank you.

245
00:16:03,970 --> 00:16:07,280
Excuse me. Have you seen this woman by any chance?

246
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,650
I can't say I have.

247
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:12,140
I see. Thank you.

248
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:16,020
Did you find her?

249
00:16:24,850 --> 00:16:26,400
Kotaro-san?

250
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,220
Oh my...

251
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:31,470
Where is my wallet?

252
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:34,930
Sorry. Just a moment.

253
00:16:36,460 --> 00:16:39,040
